    <summary>Antigravity IDE - Google's agentic, agent-first AI IDE with async parallel agents and a browser agent, powered by Gemini 3.</summary>
    <description>Antigravity IDE is the agentic development environment of Google Antigravity, built for the agent-first era and powered by Google's Gemini 3 models. It integrates AI agents directly into your workspace and gives them the tools to operate autonomously across the editor, terminal, and browser, with an emphasis on verification and higher-level communication through tasks and artifacts.

## Main features

- **AI-powered IDE** - a full AI-powered editor with the features developers rely on, including the **Agent** and **Tab** (a powerful autocomplete) modalities.
- **Asynchronous agents** - local agents that work in parallel across all of your workspaces.
- **Browser agent** - an agent that can drive the browser to accomplish dev tasks such as dashboard reads, SCM actions, and UI testing.

Agents communicate through **Artifacts** - rich markdown files, diff views, architecture diagrams, images, and browser recordings - so you can verify their work at a glance.

## This is a community-maintained package

This package downloads the official `Antigravity IDE.exe` installer directly from Google's servers. It is **not** affiliated with or endorsed by Google. "Antigravity", "Gemini" and "Google" are trademarks of Google LLC.</description>
